SLS 26RS-3018 ORIGINAL
2026 Regular Session
SENATE RESOLUTION NO. 141
BY SENATOR HODGES
RETIREMENT SYSTEMS. Requests state retirement systems to identify China-connected
holdings and to report on how to divest from such investments in a prudent and orderly
manner.
1 A RESOLUTION
2 To urge and request the boards of trustees of the state retirement systems to study and make
3 recommendations regarding refraining from investing in the securities of companies
4 domiciled in China or whose management and direction are subject to the control of
5 the Chinese government, Chinese military, or the Chinese Communist Party.
6 WHEREAS, the People's Republic of China and its controlling Communist Party are
7 progressively hostile to the interests of the United States and the state of Louisiana and are
8 actively engaged in systemic efforts to steal intellectual property, undermine democracy, and
9 undermine the individual freedoms cherished by residents of Louisiana; and
10 WHEREAS, due to ongoing tension between the United States and China, exposure
11 to investment in securities, equities, and other holdings of business entities affiliated with
12 or controlled by the Chinese government introduces regulatory and geopolitical risks that
13 may cause sudden losses for state retirement systems; and
14 WHEREAS, recognizing the risk to holders of Chinese-based equities and
15 investments due to Chinese government interference, market manipulation, and lack of
16 financial and organizational transparency, state pension funds in Arkansas, Kansas,
17 Missouri, Oklahoma, Texas, and Florida, as well as the Federal Retirement Thrift Investment
18 Board, have divested from such holdings; and
