1 WHEREAS, the Louisiana Legislature urges officials charged with the fiduciary duty
2 of managing state pension dollars to act prudently and in the best interests of state employees
3 whose retirement savings they are charged with managing.
4 THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED that the Senate of the Legislature of Louisiana
5 does hereby urge and request the boards of trustees of the state retirement systems to conduct
6 a prudent, risk-based review of existing investments in securities and other financial
7 instruments of businesses domiciled in China or otherwise subject to the control of the
8 Chinese government, Chinese military, or the Chinese Communist Party for the purpose of
9 identifying and recommending appropriate divestment of such holdings, and further requests
10 the systems to study and make recommendations regarding refraining from any future
11 investments in such companies.
12 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the boards of the Louisiana State Employees'
13 Retirement System, the Teachers' Retirement System of Louisiana, the Louisiana School
14 Employees' Retirement System, and the Louisiana State Police Retirement System shall
15 identify and quantify current holdings to determine exposure to China-connected
16 investments, meaning investments in companies or entities domiciled in China or subject to
17 the control of the Chinese government, Chinese military, or the Chinese Communist Party;
18 evaluate the material financial and operational risks associated with such exposure; examine
19 divestment in a reasonable, orderly, and prudent manner from such investments; and identify
20 internal controls that would prohibit future investments in Chinese entities or China-
21 connected investments.
22 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the executive director of each of the state
23 retirement system boards shall submit a report to the Senate Retirement Committee by
24 December 1, 2026, regarding any current holdings in companies or entities domiciled in
25 China or subject to the control of the Chinese government, Chinese military, or the Chinese
26 Communist Party.
27 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the report shall include all of the following:
28 (1) The name of each issuer and the type of security or investment vehicle.
29 (2) The market value of the holding as of a date certain.
30 (3) The percentage of the system's portfolio represented by each such holdings.
